cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.PF 

This paper deals with the performance analysis of a wireless network used by multiple event-based systems. The paper focuses on the contention resolution mechanism used by the systems to access the network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with the joint interactions of the event-triggering policy and the CRM, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper uses a Markov model to analyze the network interactions, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also presents Monte-Carlo simulations to validate the model, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the reliability of the network, which falls under the category of cs.PF (Performance).
